crutching
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the removal of wool from the head, belly and rear end of sheep, in order to keep fleece-wool clean, sheep from becoming wool-blind and allow udders to be clear for lambing.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:crutch
Pronunciation:
Notes:
